summary: This is an FBI ELSUR (Electronic Surveillance) evidence envelope form documenting the chain of custody for intercepted material. It indicates consensual monitoring intercepts related to case number 7d-Mtif--It3311, with an intercept date of January 1, 2003, and a transfer date of January 30, 2004.

events.title: Consensual monitoring intercept
events.description: Electronic surveillance intercept conducted, likely as part of an investigation.

events.title: Data transferred for permanent storage
events.description: Intercepted data from the consensual monitoring was transferred for permanent FBI storage.

keyFacts: The document is an FBI ELSUR evidence envelope, establishing chain of custody for intercepted material.
It records a consensual monitoring intercept that took place on January 1, 2003.
The intercepted data was transferred for permanent storage on January 30, 2004.
The form indicates the intercept was non-telephonic (NTCM), but the specific device used is not specified in the visible text.
